“Many brave men and women across our country proudly serve in law enforcement to protect and defend the people of this nation, and it’s important we remember them not just during #NationalPoliceWeek, but every day.”

“As the Republican Leader on CHA, it’s my honor to work closely with these officers who are ready and willing to stand in the line of fire for others. The US Capitol Police protect Members of Congress, their staffs, and millions of visitors to the Capitol complex each year.”

Ranking Member @RodneyDavis wrote an open letter to the US Capitol Police in honor of #NationalPoliceWeek. You can read his words of appreciation, posted in @thehill here: https://thehill.com/blogs/congress-blog/lawmaker-news/444148-we-owe-a-debt-of-gratitude-to-all-our-police-officers-and?rnd=1558042469 …

“My takeaway from today’s conversation with many of our county clerks is that we need to continue to keep our elections local, and the federal government needs to help them invest in technology and other methods to secure their election process.” #ElectionSecurity

Today, Ranking Member @RodneyDavis held a bipartisan Election Security Roundtable with local county clerks in his Congressional District, Illinois 13. “Election security must remain a priority.” pic.twitter.com/r4JBpXB2r3
We look forward to having more discussion on #ElectionSecurity - an issue too important to be partisan. https://twitter.com/HouseAdm_Dems/status/1126543208887062528 …

States have made tremendous strides in election security since 2016 by partnering with the federal government. If HR1 were implemented, the federal government would take over state elections, erasing their hard work. #ElectionSecurity

During the hearing @JohnHMerrill testified before the Committee saying, “It’s easier to defend an individual state system” than trying to secure one set of equipment that’s used across the nation. #ElectionSecurity
“Election security cannot be a partisan exercise, but what we saw during the markup and passage of #HR1 was purely partisan. Too much is at stake to make this about party.”

Ranking Member @RodneyDavis discusses the importance of bipartisanship when looking into our nation’s election security.

“The minority turnout surge benefited Democrats who picked up 40 House seats, seven governorships and six legislative chambers. But Democrats still blame their defeats in the FL & GA gubernatorial races on voter suppression. Census data show otherwise.”

According to @pewresearch, voter turnout in the 2018 midterm election was at an all-time high nationally.
